Q: By himself, Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. On a particular day, he happens to finish two-thirds of the work. The remaining portion of the work is done by Jill, whose rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. How long does it take Jill to finish the remaining work?
Options: (a) 4 (b) 8 (c) 22 (d) 50 (e) 20
A:
 Jack can clean the yacht in 12 hours, so his rate is 1/12 of the yacht per hour. He finishes 2/3 of the work, so he has 1/3 left. 1/3 of the yacht per hour is 1/3 * 1/12 = 1/36 of the yacht per hour. Jill's rate is 5% of this, so she can clean 1/36 * 5/100 = 1/72 of the yacht per hour. So it will take her 1/3 * 72 = 24 hours to finish the remaining work. So the answer is (b).

