Q: An express electric train takes exact three seconds to enter tunnel which is 1 mile long.
If train is traveling at 120 mile an hour, how long will it take to pass completely through the tunnel?
Options: (a) 43 seconds (b) 39 seconds (c) 20 seconds (d) 33 seconds (e) 55 seconds
A:
 The train is traveling at 120 mph. 1 mile = 5280 feet. So, the train is traveling at 120 * 5280/3600 = 176 feet per second. The train takes 3 seconds to enter the tunnel, so it is 176 * 3 = 528 feet inside the tunnel. The train will take 528/176 = 3 seconds to come out of the tunnel. So, it will take 3 + 3 = 6 seconds to pass completely through the tunnel. So the answer is (c).

